# DockPipe — agent rules (summary)

**Canonical detail:** **`AGENTS.md`** at the repo root.

## Two channels

1. **`.dockpipe/`** and **`.dorkpipe/`** — generated **context** (handoffs, self-analysis, CI signals, metrics). **Read-only** grounding. Do not auto-regenerate; refresh only when the user asks (`make self-analysis*` / `dorkpipe-self-analysis`). Compliance: **`docs/compliance-ai-handoff.md`**; scans: **`docs/dorkpipe-ci-signals.md`**.

2. **MCP (`mcpd`)** — **Bounded tools** with tiers **`DOCKPIPE_MCP_TIER`** (`readonly` → `validate` → `exec`). Default is **`validate`** (no `dockpipe.run` / `dorkpipe.run_spec`). Tier **`exec`** enables run tools. **`docs/mcp-agent-trust.md`**, **`docs/mcp-architecture.md`**.

## Isolation (DockPipe workflows)

Self-analysis and other workflows still run in **Docker-isolated** steps per **`shipyard/workflows/`** — that path is **unchanged**; it is not “the MCP connection doing Docker.”

## Compliance / governance questions

Follow **`docs/compliance-ai-handoff.md`**; prefer **`.dockpipe/ci-analysis/`**, **`.dorkpipe/self-analysis/`** when present; never invent scan results.
